claim.claim-text:
10. A table saw, comprising: 
a work support table having upper and lower surfaces, the work support table defining a slot therethrough, the upper surface defining at least one guide groove oriented generally parallel to the slot; 
a pair of trunnions attached to the lower surface of the work support table, at least one of the trunnions defining an adjustment opening having opposing sides; 
a cradle assembly having a blade mounted therein, the cradle assembly being supported by the trunnions such that at least a portion of the blade extends through the slot in the work support surface; and 
an adjustment member received by the adjustment opening in the trunnion, the adjustment member being rotatably attached to the lower surface of the work support table; 
such that rotation of the adjustment member causes the adjustment member to contact one of the opposing sides of the adjustment opening, thus moving the trunnion to adjust the position of the blade relative to the guide groove.
